item.title: FL STUDIO MOBILE | Getting Started
item.dc:creator: Image Line Software
item.description: FL Studio Mobile: 3.2.19 is now available for Android, iOS and Windows. Now with time signatures.
item.content:encoded:
FL STUDIO MOBILE| Is the dark horse of the Image Line stable. It has remained in the top 3 best selling DAW Apps on the Android, iOS and Windows stores for the last 5 years. Most often found in the #1 spot. FL Studio Mobile has the widest hardware compatibility of any mobile-first DAW working on Phones (Android & iOS), Tablets (Android, iOS & Windows) and Laptops (Chrome OS, macOS & Windows). It's also a plugin in FL Studio so you can download the Trial version any time and try it for yourself.

Read the manual or watch all the FL Studio Mobile tutorial videos here.

No matter where you are or what hardware platform you choose, FL Studio Mobile is there ready to support your best creative moments.

item.title: FL STUDIO | History of the Fruit
item.dc:creator: Image Line Software
item.description: FL STUDIO | Many people ask us what fruit is the logo? The original concept was designed by Didier Dambrin (gol), the inventor of FL Studio and was based on a Strawberry. Didier says "The strawberry was a fail, the (second) one was too based on pixel art, then scaled...
item.content:encoded:
FL STUDIO | Many people ask us what fruit is the logo? The original concept was designed by Didier Dambrin (gol), the inventor of FL Studio and was based on a Strawberry. Didier says "The strawberry was a fail, the (second) one was too based on pixel art, then scaled up vector-like. At that point it was still supposed to be a Strawberry I guess, it's only in 3D that it didn't look like one anymore". After that the fruit logo took on a life of its own, evolving into a cross between a Mango and Strawberry. We think it now looks closest to a Persimmon. Whatever the fruit is, we're glad to know it brings a smile to millions of people, world wide, every month.

 

The 'modern' FL Studio fruit under construction in 3D Max in 2002

item.title: FLEX | Essential Guitars & Bass (FREE)
item.dc:creator: Image Line Software
item.description: FLEX | We are excited to announce two free FLEX libraries for FL Studio owners. Essential Guitars & Essential Bass guitars. Just open FLEX and under the FREE tab in the library browser on the left click the download icons for each library. Learn more about FLEX here   Essential...
item.content:encoded:
FLEX | We are excited to announce two free FLEX libraries for FL Studio owners. Essential Guitars & Essential Bass guitars. Just open FLEX and under the FREE tab in the library browser on the left click the download icons for each library.

Learn more about FLEX here

 

Essential Guitars | Multisampled electric and acoustic guitars by sound designer Saif Sameer.

45 Presets / 278 MB.

Essential Bass Guitars | Multisampled electric bass guitars by sound designer Saif Sameer.

50 Presets / 391 MB

About the libraries ...

Based on Directwave Axe Forge & Bass Mace libraries, enhanced with added details, processing and FLEX specific features by sound designer Saif Sameer. Physical modelling technique used to add round robin variations to repeated notes for greater realism.
Nuances such as fret noises, scratches, slides and string buzz provided by power-user & artist Johannes aka Umziky. All adjustable through FLEX macro parameters. Presets include various pick up, cabinet and guitar pedal effect simulations at a low CPU impact. Note slide or vibrato articulations simply triggered by high velocity note input.

NOTE: The Essential Guitars and Bass Guitars libraries require FL Studio 20.8 or later. Open FLEX and the FREE tab to download them.

Image-Line

item.description: FL STUDIO | With the frequent Covid 19 related lockdowns, online streaming has seen a huge growth over the 2020-2021 period. It's no surprise then, that FL Studio is one of the most popular DAWs on YouTube and Twitch for music production streamers. The most confusing part for most people...
item.content:encoded:
FL STUDIO | With the frequent Covid 19 related lockdowns, online streaming has seen a huge growth over the 2020-2021 period. It's no surprise then, that FL Studio is one of the most popular DAWs on YouTube and Twitch for music production streamers. The most confusing part for most people is getting Audio Loopback from FL Studio into OBS (Open Broadcaster Software) inside the computer. In this tutorial we show how to sort the Audio Input for macOS and Windows.

Visit FL TUDIO @ YouTube

Remember, stream responsibly! ??
